The paper deals with the capacity-equivocation region of a cognitive interference channel with confidential messages, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the Gaussian case, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). The concept of secrecy and eavesdropping is relevant to network security (cs.NI) and the cognitive aspect of the channel may relate to machine learning or artificial intelligence (cs.SI).
